{Module Data/Docs/Introduction
  {Exports IntroductionDoc}
  {Defs
    {IntroductionDoc
      Div(:class "prose prose-invert max-w-none"
        Div(:class "space-y-8"
          ; Hero Section
          Div(:class "space-y-4"
            H1(:class "text-5xl font-bold bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-400 to-blue-500 bg-clip-text text-transparent"
              "Introduction to Syma"
            )
            P(:class "text-xl text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
              "Welcome to Syma ‚Äî a symbolic term-rewriting language that reimagines programming through pattern matching and normalization."
            )
          )

          ; What is Syma
          Div(:class "space-y-4"
            H2(:class "text-3xl font-bold text-gray-200" "What is Syma?")
            P(:class "text-gray-300 leading-relaxed"
              "Syma is a symbolic programming language based on "
              Span(:class "text-cyan-400 font-semibold" "term rewriting")
              ". Unlike traditional languages where you write functions that execute, in Syma you write "
              Span(:class "text-cyan-400 font-semibold" "rules")
              " that "
              Span(:class "text-cyan-400 font-semibold" "match patterns")
              " and "
              Span(:class "text-cyan-400 font-semibold" "rewrite terms")
              ". The runtime repeatedly applies these rules until the program reaches a stable state ‚Äî called a "
              Span(:class "text-cyan-400 font-semibold" "normal form")
              "."
            )

            Div(:class "bg-yellow-900/20 border border-yellow-700/50 rounded-lg p-6"
              Div(:class "flex gap-3"
                Div(:class "text-2xl" "‚ö†Ô∏è")
                Div(:class "space-y-2"
                  P(:class "font-semibold text-yellow-400" "Important: Syma is NOT Lisp")
                  P(:class "text-gray-300 leading-relaxed"
                    "Syma may look superficially Lisp-like because of its minimal syntax, but it's fundamentally different. "
                    "In Lisp, you evaluate functions. In Syma, you rewrite trees. "
                    "There is no eval, no environment, no call stack, no macroexpansion ‚Äî only pattern matching and normalization."
                  )
                  P(:class "text-gray-300 leading-relaxed"
                    "In spirit, Syma is closer to Maude, ELAN, and Wolfram Mathematica, but built as a general-purpose programming language."
                  )
                )
              )
            )
          )

          ; Key Features
          Div(:class "space-y-4"
            H2(:class "text-3xl font-bold text-gray-200" "Key Features")
            Div(:class "grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4"
              Div(:class "p-6 bg-gray-900/50 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg"
                Div(:class "text-3xl mb-3" "üîÑ")
                H3(:class "text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2" "Term Rewriting")
                P(:class "text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
                  "Rules match patterns and rewrite terms. Computation is normalization until the structure stabilizes."
                )
              )
              Div(:class "p-6 bg-gray-900/50 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg"
                Div(:class "text-3xl mb-3" "üéØ")
                H3(:class "text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2" "Pattern Matching")
                P(:class "text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
                  "Powerful pattern matching with variables, rest patterns, regex, alternation, and greedy anchors."
                )
              )
              Div(:class "p-6 bg-gray-900/50 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg"
                Div(:class "text-3xl mb-3" "üß©")
                H3(:class "text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2" "Homoiconic")
                P(:class "text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
                  "Code is data is runtime. Rules can rewrite other rules. Build DSLs, type systems, and paradigms as libraries."
                )
              )
              Div(:class "p-6 bg-gray-900/50 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg"
                Div(:class "text-3xl mb-3" "üåê")
                H3(:class "text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2" "Multiplatform")
                P(:class "text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"
                  "Runs in browsers, Node.js, and beyond. Same code everywhere with platform-agnostic effects."
                )
              )
            )
          )

          ; Quick Example
          Div(:class "space-y-4"
            H2(:class "text-3xl font-bold text-gray-200" "Your First Syma Program")
            P(:class "text-gray-300 leading-relaxed"
              "Here's a simple example showing Syma's term rewriting in action:"
            )
            Div(:class "bg-gray-950 border border-gray-800 rounded-xl p-6 overflow-x-auto"
              Pre(:class "font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed"
                Code(
                  Span(:class "text-gray-500" "; Define a rule to add unary numbers\n")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "{")
                  Span(:class "text-cyan-500" "R ")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-600" "\"AddUnary\"\n")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "  {")
                  Span(:class "text-cyan-500" "Add ")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "{")
                  Span(:class "text-cyan-500" "Unary ")
                  Span(:class "text-purple-400" "a..")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "} {")
                  Span(:class "text-cyan-500" "Unary ")
                  Span(:class "text-purple-400" "b..")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "}}\n")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "  {")
                  Span(:class "text-cyan-500" "Unary ")
                  Span(:class "text-purple-400" "a.. b..")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "}\n")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "}\n\n")
                  Span(:class "text-gray-500" "; Use it\n")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "{")
                  Span(:class "text-cyan-500" "Add ")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "{")
                  Span(:class "text-cyan-500" "Unary ")
                  Span(:class "text-white" "| | |")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "} {")
                  Span(:class "text-cyan-500" "Unary ")
                  Span(:class "text-white" "| |")
                  Span(:class "text-yellow-400" "}}\n")
                  Span(:class "text-gray-500" "; ‚Üí {Unary | | | | |}")
                )
              )
            )
            P(:class "text-gray-300 leading-relaxed"
              "This rule matches two unary numbers and combines them by concatenating their contents. "
              "The "
              Span(:class "text-cyan-400 font-mono" "a..")
              " and "
              Span(:class "text-cyan-400 font-mono" "b..")
              " are "
              Span(:class "text-cyan-400 font-semibold" "rest variables")
              " that match zero or more elements."
            )
          )

          ; Next Steps
          Div(:class "space-y-4"
            H2(:class "text-3xl font-bold text-gray-200" "Next Steps")
            Div(:class "grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4"
              A(:href "/docs/installation" :class "group block p-6 bg-gray-900/50 border border-gray-800 hover:border-cyan-700 rounded-lg transition-all"
                Div(:class "text-3xl mb-3" "üì¶")
                H3(:class "text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-400 group-hover:text-cyan-300 mb-2" "Installation")
                P(:class "text-gray-400 text-sm" "Get Syma installed on your system")
              )
              A(:href "/docs/term-rewriting" :class "group block p-6 bg-gray-900/50 border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 rounded-lg transition-all"
                Div(:class "text-3xl mb-3" "üîÑ")
                H3(:class "text-xl font-semibold text-blue-400 group-hover:text-blue-300 mb-2" "Term Rewriting")
                P(:class "text-gray-400 text-sm" "Learn the core concept behind Syma")
              )
              A(:href "/docs/syntax" :class "group block p-6 bg-gray-900/50 border border-gray-800 hover:border-purple-700 rounded-lg transition-all"
                Div(:class "text-3xl mb-3" "üìñ")
                H3(:class "text-xl font-semibold text-purple-400 group-hover:text-purple-300 mb-2" "Syntax Guide")
                P(:class "text-gray-400 text-sm" "Master Syma's syntax and structure")
              )
            )
          )
        )
      )
    }
  }
}
